<TITLE> BNP observing mass sit-in </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 9 (bdnews24.com)  Opposition BNP is observing a four-hour mass sit-in at the Institution of Engineers Bangladesh in Dhaka on Wednesday protesting the government's "interference in the judicial system". The programme started from 10:30am. BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia announced the programme at a rally in Dhaka last month. This is the first BNP-led four-party opposition's anti-government protest since the Awami League came to power in January 2009. The allies Jamaat-e-Islami, Islami Oikya Jote and Bangladesh Jatiya Party (BJP) have also joined the programme. Leaders and activists of the four-party alliance were gathering at the venue with procession from 10am. A large police and Rapid Action Battalion presence has been deployed around the area. A stage has been set up at the Institution premises. Microphones have been installed from Shahbagh through to Kadam fountain. Khaleda attended the programme as chief guest. Among the BNP senior leaders were Khandaker Delwar Hossain, Khandaker Mosharraf Hossain, Moudud Ahmed, Tariqul Islam, MK Anwar, ASM Hannan Shah, Goyeshwar Chandra Roy, Rafikul Islam Miah, Nazrul Islam Khan, Mirza Fakhrul Islam Alamgir and Sadeque Hossain Khoka. Among the leaders of the allies were Islami Oikya Jote secretary general Abdul Latif Nezami, Bangladesh Jatiya Party chairman Andalib Rahman Partha and secretary general Shamim Al Mamun. Dhaka, June 9 (bdnews24.com)  Opposition BNP is observing a four-hour mass sit-in at the Institute of Engineers Bangladesh in Dhaka on Wednesday protesting the government's interference in the judicial system. The programme started from 10:30am with the reading of extracts from the holy Quran. BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia announced the programme at a rally in Dhaka last month. This is the first BNP-led four-party opposition anti-government protest since the Awami League came to power in January 2009. The allies Jamaat-e-Islami, Islami Oikyojote and Bangladesh Jatiya Party (BJP) have also joined the programm